ETYMOLOGY. Named after the Afar (
Afar: Qafár
) people, also known as the Danakil and Adal, an ethnic group inhabiting the Horn of Africa. They reside primarily in the Afar Region of Ethiopia and northern Djibouti , although some also live in the southern end of Eritrea . The Afars speak the Afar language, which is part of the Cushitic branch of the Afro-Asiatic family. Both recorded localities of this species are within their territory.
